In this article, President Joe Biden acknowledges and honors the contributions of public servants in America during Public Service Recognition Week. He highlights the crucial role they play in education, public safety, national defense, healthcare, infrastructure, and more. He praises the resilience and dedication of public servants during the COVID-19 pandemic and mentions the financial support provided by the American Rescue Plan. President Biden expresses his commitment to protecting and empowering the federal workforce, including increasing the minimum wage for federal employees and promoting diversity and inclusion. He also mentions efforts to provide relief to public servants with federal student loans. The article concludes with President Biden proclaiming May 1 to May 7, 2022, as Public Service Recognition Week and calling upon all Americans to celebrate public servants' contributions.